  "name": "ssign",
  "identifier": "ssign",
  "description": "ssign is a bioinformatics pipeline that identifies secretion-system substrates in Gram-negative bacterial genomes. It combines secretion-system detection (MacSyFinder v2 + TXSScan), secreted-protein prediction (DeepLocPro, DeepSecE, PLM-Effector, SignalP), per-component genomic proximity analysis, and multi-tool functional annotation (BLASTp, HH-suite, InterProScan, Bakta, EggNOG, pLM-BLAST, ProtParam) to generate a ranked, evidence-linked list of candidate substrates together with a summary HTML report and intermediate tables.",
